WEBVTT

00:00:00.120 --> 00:00:06.519
Hey, good morning, family! I'm excited to be with you all today. I brought my best friend, Diana, on here—my wife.

00:00:06.520 --> 00:00:10.939
She's the behind-the-scenes person; she's been there answering the emails.

00:00:10.940 --> 00:00:19.558
I brought her on before in a past video but never really let her talk a lot about our life and how we make things work.

00:00:19.559 --> 00:00:42.552
We get a lot of emails from people saying, 'My marriage is falling apart,''I'm in shambles here,'or 'My kids are backsliding or going to hell.'Email after email, and I feel in my heart it's time to talk about how to put God first place in your home.

00:00:42.553 --> 00:00:50.378
I can honestly tell you all, if you are not putting God first place in your house, you're not going to make it.

00:00:50.379 --> 00:01:05.639
There are nights you don't want to pray and you're just ready to go to bed, but you say, 'Hold on, this is priority.'I don't care how tired we are, we're going to pray and go before the Father for our children and seek Him.

00:01:05.640 --> 00:01:13.771
Even when we're dead tired, where you feel like you've worked all day and don't feel like doing this, how bad is your 'want-to'?

00:01:13.772 --> 00:01:25.397
Do you want your children to know how to live by faith whenever they get older? Do you want your marriage to be strong?

00:01:25.398 --> 00:01:33.259
Putting God first, taking communion daily—we take communion daily and pray together every day.

00:01:33.260 --> 00:01:42.580
We read our Bible and listen to the Word all the time. It's so much so that I don't even realize I do it.

00:01:42.581 --> 00:01:52.607
Even as the head of the house, I'm always continually praying, singing, or inviting Him into our home.

00:01:52.608 --> 00:02:13.064
Being a leader, man, being a leader of your home, praying with your wife and your children before they go to bed, anointing them with oil—doing the things you can do as a leader.

00:02:13.065 --> 00:02:23.448
They say 70 to 75% of all marriages with special needs children end in divorce, and 50% of all Body of Christ marriages end in divorce.

00:02:23.449 --> 00:02:31.799
Here we are, working together. Back whenever I got laid off at the church, I worked there for so long.

00:02:31.800 --> 00:02:40.272
When they came to me and said—because our pastor fell morally and they couldn't afford to keep a lot of the staff on—they eliminated a lot of things.

00:02:40.273 --> 00:02:46.543
So, we stepped out by faith and started doing our business selling online just seeking Him.

00:02:46.544 --> 00:03:14.410
The Lord said, 'Brandon, I'm going to speak to you every single day and show you things at thrift stores; I'm going to show you where to find provision for that day.'She quit her job because, as I said, she had a master's degree, finished with a 4.0 in college, and graduated top of the class summa cum laude.

00:03:14.411 --> 00:03:23.352
'Yeah, I graduated from university while we had little kids.

00:03:23.353 --> 00:03:36.779
It was really a lot to do, but it was a way we were trying to find the path that God had for us.

00:03:36.780 --> 00:03:46.643
Then we started doing the thrift store thing, and that was the path that God blessed in our life.

00:03:46.644 --> 00:03:59.751
It was just going to a thrift store and finding stuff, and that was our provision for the day. I remember when it first started, the Lord gave me the idea.

00:03:59.752 --> 00:04:06.413
We didn't have enough money to last us through that month, and Brandon and I were talking about it.

00:04:06.415 --> 00:04:23.077
You were like, "It's the month of May and we don't have enough money to pay all our bills."So I went to God in prayer about it and asked for a miracle or a creative idea.

00:04:23.078 --> 00:04:34.927
He brought to my mind the idea of finding something at a thrift store that would hold a profit and selling it online.

00:04:34.928 --> 00:04:38.046
The Lord really blessed that, and that's how we got through that month.

00:04:38.047 --> 00:04:50.799
The Lord just breathed on little things like that, and that's how we've lived our life: staying in prayer, taking communion every day.

00:04:50.800 --> 00:04:59.566
Whenever you stay rooted and grounded in God, He blesses you in the little areas.

00:04:59.567 --> 00:05:07.373
He's always provided for us. If we have a problem or a need, we ask God what to do.

00:05:07.374 --> 00:05:20.637
We tell Him we're at the end of our rope, and He's never early, He's never late—He always shows up right on time for us.

00:05:20.638 --> 00:05:28.865
Even in everything.'Yeah, it was that way even like what she was talking about in May.

00:05:28.866 --> 00:05:37.994
It was thousands of dollars we needed to pay our bills after I got laid off from the church. I thought, 'God, this isn't fair.

00:05:37.995 --> 00:05:47.381
How are we going to get through this?'You can feel sorry for yourself and whine, but that isn't going to get you anywhere.

00:05:47.382 --> 00:05:53.417
God is not moved by your need; He's moved by your faith and by a seed.

00:05:53.418 --> 00:05:57.940
When you have seedtime and harvest, when you sow, you'll reap.

00:05:57.941 --> 00:06:10.629
A lot of people think they're helpless and just sit back, but the Bible says whatever you put your hands to will prosper.

00:06:10.630 --> 00:06:17.752
He gives you the power to get wealth; He never told you to sit back and just let God do things.

00:06:17.753 --> 00:06:27.756
No, He gave you dominion and authority on this Earth. So, we don't have a mailbox mentality of looking for a handout.

00:06:27.757 --> 00:06:47.602
We don't say, 'Lord, help us, we need a Holy Ghost handshake today at church; please somebody give us a hundred dollars.'I never one time sat there and whined about money because I realized what my Covenant says.

00:06:47.603 --> 00:06:51.700
He said He's never seen the righteous forsaken nor his seed begging bread.

00:06:51.701 --> 00:07:04.342
I said, 'Lord, if you said whatever I put my hands to would prosper and you give me creative ideas to get wealth, you're going to give it to us.'I was the one praying and fasting, and guess who He spoke to?

00:07:04.343 --> 00:07:23.670
My best friend. She came to me and said, 'Brandon, I have an idea,'and my response back was, 'That's crazy, that's not going to work.'But I felt like God told me this.

00:07:23.671 --> 00:07:30.788
When the Holy Spirit speaks to you, it's that still, small voice.

00:07:30.789 --> 00:07:43.657
'I haven't had visitations like you, but I've always been led by that still, small voice of the Holy Spirit leading and guiding me.

00:07:43.658 --> 00:08:04.499
Even when my kids were born, we didn't have money to pay the hospital bills, and we would just believe God by faith that they would be paid. He always came through. He's never early, He's never late.

00:08:04.500 --> 00:08:15.796
Even in finding provision, I've always tried to be a Proverbs 31 wife, taking the resources we have and making them stretch as far as possible.

00:08:15.797 --> 00:08:34.304
I would go to garage sales for everything—baby blankets, baby bottles—just finding them used because God gives you resources.

00:08:34.305 --> 00:08:41.044
You don't just go buy everything new; you make it stretch as far as you can.

00:08:41.045 --> 00:08:49.266
If you're faithful with the little, He will make you ruler over much.

00:08:49.267 --> 00:09:08.012
We've lived so frugally, buying everything used and going to garage sales. It's thinking, "How do I find the best deal?

00:09:08.013 --> 00:09:26.134
Lord, lead me to find that deal."He's always helped me.'But it was even whenever you came to me and told me the idea for selling online.

00:09:26.135 --> 00:09:40.025
I thought there was no way that was going to work, but I trusted the Holy Ghost inside of her just as much as she trusted the Holy Ghost inside of me.

00:09:40.026 --> 00:09:46.103
It took me humbling myself and saying, 'Okay, I trust the voice of the Lord inside of you, babe.

00:09:46.104 --> 00:09:54.416
Let's try it. What do we have to lose?'So we had a hundred dollars and went to the thrift store.

00:09:54.417 --> 00:10:02.340
We bought the things the Lord put on our hearts to buy, and we were able to pay our electric bill.

00:10:02.341 --> 00:10:13.972
I said, 'Wow, it worked!'So I took another fifty dollars and bought more stuff.

00:10:13.973 --> 00:10:21.561
Every single time I pray, the Lord shows me a shirt or something in the thrift store.

00:10:21.562 --> 00:10:37.638
He would lead me and say, 'It's over off this street; go to this one.'I'd tell Diana, 'Babe, I had a vision; if you go into this store, this shirt is in there.'I'd name the brand and what it looks like.

00:10:37.639 --> 00:10:53.103
She'd go in looking for the item and find it. We'd list it and sell it within a week, and we were able to pay our bills again.

00:10:53.104 --> 00:11:05.373
That's the way we've lived our life for seven years now—living by faith for every single thing and asking for favor.

00:11:05.374 --> 00:11:18.337
'Lord, give us favor with the thrift store owners and favor at the garage sale today.'When we go through the garage sales, we go through the rich neighborhoods and ask the Lord where to go.

00:11:18.338 --> 00:11:31.638
You become desperate for hearing Him, and He will start speaking to you on a daily basis.

00:11:31.639 --> 00:11:44.172
Now we teach our kids how to live by faith and believe God. We believe with all our hearts that tithing and giving are for today.

00:11:44.173 --> 00:11:59.597
My life is an example of being at the bottom of the barrel and coming out on top.

00:11:59.598 --> 00:12:13.085
This year we didn't struggle like we did being janitors at the church, barely making it.

00:12:13.086 --> 00:12:24.773
There's so much financial stress today, but when you make God a priority, He makes you a priority.

00:12:24.774 --> 00:12:36.398
He is an ever-present help in a time of need. You've got to keep your marriage strong.

00:12:36.399 --> 00:12:46.946
You've got to make peace a priority in your home and keep strife out, because strife is a cancer.

00:12:46.947 --> 00:13:02.057
When you allow the enemy to come in through strife, it is a major blockage to financial overflow and the flow of the Holy Spirit.

00:13:02.058 --> 00:13:11.430
Make peace and joy the umpire of your life. The Bible says where there is strife, there is every evil work.

00:13:11.431 --> 00:13:59.797
We're not always perfect; I come across cranky some days. We're just human, but we have decided with all our hearts to make Jesus a priority and stand in the gap.

00:13:59.798 --> 00:14:11.735
Abraham said, 'I'm not going to let any man say he made me rich; only God.'God is our source and our provider; He's our Jehovah Jireh.

00:14:11.736 --> 00:14:45.657
We also started doing therapy dogs to help kids with special needs. It's a joy to see kids or elderly people get a dog.

00:14:45.658 --> 00:15:02.796
It's been a blessing working for yourself instead of 'working for the man.'God gives creative ideas.

00:15:02.797 --> 00:15:13.152
Being willing and obedient, you eat the good of the land. In both cases, the Lord spoke to her.

00:15:13.153 --> 00:15:29.879
She said, 'Brandon, this is what I believe the Lord has shown me,'and it's been big-picture things that changed the course of our lives.

00:15:29.880 --> 00:15:44.516
I'll get the small-picture things or visions of the future, but the Lord uses her in dreams to give her ideas.

00:15:44.517 --> 00:15:54.131
That's what it should be in a marriage; it's not a one-man show. You guys have to be a team.

00:15:54.132 --> 00:16:01.932
It's not, 'I'm the alpha male, hear me roar.'You are a covenant joint.

00:16:01.933 --> 00:16:33.618
If it's a one-man show, you're not going to win any games. Don't put God in a box.

00:16:33.619 --> 00:16:52.799
A lot of people feel like money can only come through a family member or a friend of the church.

00:16:52.800 --> 00:17:06.168
When you close yourself off like that, you're not open to hearing Him.

00:17:06.169 --> 00:17:29.979
He has no limits; He is infinite and mighty. He cares about the smallest needs.

00:17:29.980 --> 00:18:09.038
I've always said, 'God, I'm open to any way you choose to help us.'Usually, it's something we can use our hands to do because the Bible says He blesses the work of our hands. I journal to God and tell Him my desires.

00:18:09.039 --> 00:18:56.003
It's important to write down your prayer requests because if you only think about the big things, you won't notice that He's been there answering a hundred small prayers throughout the year—like a new pair of sneakers or losing ten pounds.

00:18:56.004 --> 00:19:44.113
If you don't write it down, you'll miss it. Every year in January, we set out a list of what we're believing God for.

00:19:44.114 --> 00:20:11.154
It could be a vacation or a house. We push as hard as we can to believe for that.

00:20:11.155 --> 00:20:26.352
We put Megan on the list every year—for her to be completely whole and restored.

00:20:26.353 --> 00:20:32.037
We even put down for her to be potty trained; she's getting there, though she still has accidents.

00:20:32.038 --> 00:21:10.270
We look at where we came from. We're believing for a new house right now that's bigger and has a special room for Megan.

00:21:10.271 --> 00:21:31.025
Write it down at the beginning of the year. For your marriage, thank Him that it will be stronger at the end of the year.

00:21:31.026 --> 00:21:46.374
If you're single and believing for a godly spouse, write down the characteristics and qualities.

00:21:46.375 --> 00:21:59.739
Brandon and I both did that before we ever met. I was thirteen when I wrote it down.

00:21:59.740 --> 00:22:35.333
I would pray over him before I even knew who he was—praying that God would keep him pure and on fire for Him.

00:22:35.334 --> 00:22:55.117
I strongly believe the protection I've had in my life was because he prayed over me before he ever met me.

00:22:55.118 --> 00:23:27.728
After we got married, we showed each other our lists. I wrote down the personality type and everything. I said, 'Father, I'm not settling for an Ishmael.

00:23:27.729 --> 00:24:06.158
I want my Isaac.'Interestingly, my parents felt called to move to Fort Worth, Texas, to go to Bible school, and that's where I met her.

00:24:06.159 --> 00:24:43.319
The footsteps of the righteous are ordered by the Lord. If it wasn't for keeping God a priority, we would have been divorced a long time ago.

00:24:43.320 --> 00:25:11.639
It hasn't always been easy, but we are quick to repent. If I have a bad attitude, I say, 'I'm sorry.'I want to have a soft heart.

00:25:11.640 --> 00:25:28.461
The Holy Spirit will rebuke me and say, 'You need to go back and make that right.'He's always got her back.

00:25:28.462 --> 00:25:44.112
I'll go to her and say, 'Babe, the Holy Spirit just corrected me on how I talked to you, and I apologize.'She's glad He cares about her like that.

00:25:44.113 --> 00:26:17.840
Let the Lord be the captain of your life. You drive the car, but let Him be the pilot.

00:26:17.841 --> 00:26:25.953
I refuse to let my intellect lead me because the carnal man knows not the things of the Lord.

00:26:25.954 --> 00:26:51.813
I want to be controlled by the Holy Spirit. He will make every path straight.

00:26:51.814 --> 00:27:03.460
We don't have enough time on this Earth to keep making bad choices.

00:27:03.461 --> 00:27:35.065
Every day counts. Intellect and thinking you know the way can get you in trouble.

00:27:35.066 --> 00:27:45.959
Knowledge sometimes gets in the way because you feel like you don't need Him.

00:27:45.960 --> 00:28:23.083
That's when things don't work. We just wanted to come on today and be real about marriage.

00:28:23.084 --> 00:28:32.178
I hope this blessed you. Father, we thank you for every married couple watching this.

00:28:32.179 --> 00:28:40.433
We pray a blessing over their marriage. No weapon formed against them shall prosper.

00:28:40.434 --> 00:28:54.558
Satan, we take authority over you in the name of Jesus and bind you off their homes and finances.

00:28:54.559 --> 00:29:24.199
Get off their children! We are seated with Jesus Christ in heavenly places.

00:29:24.200 --> 00:29:42.383
We command you to bow your knee and get out of our houses. We call for healing and wholeness.

00:29:42.384 --> 00:29:53.384
If a marriage is in jeopardy, we pray peace and deliverance.

00:29:53.385 --> 00:30:32.918
You are the restorer of all things. We call the children home in Jesus'name.

00:30:32.919 --> 00:30:42.177
We take our covenant rights. We are so grateful for everything You did on that cross.

00:30:42.178 --> 00:30:58.083
I speak to breast cancer right now and command it to leave in the name of Jesus.

00:30:58.084 --> 00:31:48.053
I curse lumps and call for healing over that woman's body. I call ovaries healed in the name of Jesus.

00:31:48.054 --> 00:31:55.202
If you're not able to have a baby, I speak to your womb right now and call it to be filled.

00:31:55.203 --> 00:32:33.848
We know the Word says our vine will not cast fruit before the time. We lay hold to children right now.

00:32:33.849 --> 00:32:47.507
If there is a man with a seed problem, we call him to be healed so his body produces what it needs to have a child.

00:32:47.508 --> 00:33:05.988
I speak to that uterus and command it to be whole. We stand in agreement for a full-term healthy delivery.

00:33:05.989 --> 00:34:25.122
We believe and receive that. We call for better jobs, raises, bonuses, and inheritances.

00:34:25.123 --> 00:34:33.314
Great blessing is on their homes. Well, I feel good with that.

00:34:33.315 --> 00:34:58.448
We did good, babe. Put a smile on your face and a song in your heart. Jesus loves you, and we'll see you next time. Bye-bye!

